metadata.name: Consequences #10
metadata.description:
"Consequences"

Inspired by simple shapes, textiles, and the shapes of nature, mountains, and hills, while maintaining a minimalist style of composition and an emphasis on iridescent colors.

There are more than 252 colors that are perfectly combined with each other and give out a very interesting and unique composition. 

"We all make choices, but in the end, our choices make us."
― Ken Levin

Open it in "live" and press "s" to download in 2000x5000

Made with p5Js library.
September 2022

metadata.name: =DMT= #378
metadata.description:
The Spirit Molecule, an experience out of this world, available in this world.

What will you see when you take your =DMT=? I wish you a great trip.

Groups of color palettes, lines and bezier curves combine to create what sometimes looks like a sun, an eye, a flower, an explosion, a pair of wings or a combination of these.

I hope in the future Psychedelics will be accessible to people in controlled settings with professional care and support. 
The Ayahuasca ceremonies happening around the world are a good step in this direction.

Press 's' to save a 3000x3000 px PNG.

Created by UpOnlyFan in August 2022 with p5js.

@(=_=)- @brainspinky2014 ¬(=_=)7

metadata.name: Somnium #9
metadata.description:
The interpretation of dreams,
Glimmer and roar through the open air,
Hear the morning call at night,
What makes a buttercup of waters shine,
Sat down among the silent moonlight,
Dazzled turquoise life on veil of evening,
Whether a voice comes with thee,
Twirled by the sun at each other side.
_

Generative visual composition, hybrid techniques, animation, textures source created with GAN, assist by AI, layers transform in autonomous system, eclectic, colors, additional algorithm, glitch, modular patch, and combine with other elements that made with code.
_

metadata.name: The Modern Depth #55
metadata.description:
there is a new horizon that shimmers and shines

a place which never was before, but there always seemed to be. 
You can see it from the top of any slope, or at the bottom any hole; you can feel it in your bones when you're tired, or be blinded by it when its bright. 
And this is why we must climb every mountain and how we'll map out all those stars. 
A shape made from Modern Depth, standing tall in front of us all.
And all the people that see it on a walk in the woods don't flinch,
they feel a strange connection to the Modern Depth that can be found. 
And most importantly, we don't abuse it because we know how to use it.

metadata.name: Echoes of the Big Bang #41
metadata.description:
BIG BANG – A square shatters.
Tens of thousands pieces are hurled in all directions – SNAPSHOT.

Shattered according to the rules of the golden ratio.
Shift based on the Fibonacci numbers.

--
Keyboard control: Press "1" -> "5", saving the image in low -> high resolution. (It may take a while for the image to be generated in high resolution)

metadata.name: scratches & circles #73
metadata.description:
first fully coded generative artwork by @ndru_art made with p5.js

project features:
- up to 5 rows of 'scratches' at varying canvas heights & thickness
- scratches generated with random horizontal density and variance
- circles of varying sizes generated within a certain proximity of each row
- 5 different color palettes
- 'narrow scratches' feature defined by rows with a thickness value < 10

minters get 10% of secondary sales

special thanks to Orr Kislev for making his 'sketchy lines' code publicly available
